A random-playlist shoutcast server written in Erlang as an OTP application.

To use this bad boy:

1. Put some songs in the songs folder in project root

2. run make in root folder (to compile and open up a shell)

3. cd into ebin (inside erlang shell), then application:start(shoutcast).

4. In vlc media player (or other shoutcast player) open network stream at: http://localhost:3000

** Keep an eye on the terminal for the output. It will notify you of:

** Connect with as many clients as you like and observer synchronisation of media


